# xkillr

## License
`xkillr` is licensed under the GNU General Public License v2 or later. See [COPYING](COPYING) for details.

## About
`xkillr` is essentially a replacement for `ps aux | grep <proc>`. It provides a TUI for searching and
killing processes.

## Compile
`xkillr` uses `autotools`, so do the usual:

```
autoreconf --install && mkdir build && cd build
./configure --prefix=<loc>
make
```

where `loc` is the destination prefix for the binary i.e., `--prefix=/usr`, `--prefix=/usr/local`.

## Install
To install, do
```
make install
```

Do `make uninstall` to uninstall.
